1
00:01:31,050 --> 00:01:34,979
[Dream of Golden Years]

2
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:39,479
[2006]

3
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:04,350
Ms. Tian, please go back.

4
00:02:04,350 --> 00:02:05,070
Haven't I made it

5
00:02:05,070 --> 00:02:06,200
very clear to you?

6
00:02:06,310 --> 00:02:07,090
Go back. Just go back.

7
00:02:07,090 --> 00:02:08,630
My uncle can marry into your family.

8
00:02:08,630 --> 00:02:09,710
You won't lose anything,

9
00:02:09,710 --> 00:02:10,190
right?

10
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:11,560
Your uncle...

11
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,400
Let me tell you,

12
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,490
he's a drunkard.

13
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:14,430
He beat his wife, too.

14
00:02:14,430 --> 00:02:15,260
With conditions like that,

15
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:16,300
how could he possibly come to our house

16
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:17,050
to propose?

17
00:02:17,079 --> 00:02:17,560
Right?

18
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:19,520
Fen.

19
00:02:19,750 --> 00:02:20,180
Look.

20
00:02:20,430 --> 00:02:22,079
Xiaolan will get married sooner or later,

21
00:02:22,079 --> 00:02:22,560
right?

22
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:23,960
Whether Xiaolan gets married or not,

23
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:24,710
what does it have to do with your family?

24
00:02:24,710 --> 00:02:25,910
How is it not related?

25
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:27,240
My uncle is quite nice.

26
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:29,120
He and Fen are a good match.

27
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:31,120
I tell you, don't make random matches.

28
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:32,310
As I told you, they're not suitable.

29
00:02:32,310 --> 00:02:33,570
I'm not making random—

30
00:02:33,980 --> 00:02:35,079
Why are there so many people?

31
00:02:35,079 --> 00:02:35,800
It's quite lively.

32
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:37,680
What are you doing? You damn old woman!

33
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:38,400
Sorry.

34
00:02:38,890 --> 00:02:39,930
Alright, go back.

35
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:41,610
I've made it very clear to you.

36
00:02:41,610 --> 00:02:42,810
Go back. Just go back.

37
00:02:43,030 --> 00:02:45,030
As I told you, they're not suitable.

38
00:02:45,150 --> 00:02:45,680
Right?

39
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:47,280
You look down on my uncle?

40
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:48,960
I'd like to see what kind of family

41
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,220
Liu Fen can marry into.

42
00:02:50,750 --> 00:02:52,120
What the hell?

43
00:02:52,310 --> 00:02:53,590
She splashed water all over me!

44
00:02:53,590 --> 00:02:54,960
You are afraid of offending

45
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:56,430
these neighbors.

46
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,430
I'm all alone.

47
00:02:59,190 --> 00:03:00,050
I'm not afraid.

48
00:03:00,620 --> 00:03:01,820
Granny Yu, well done.

49
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:04,280
Well,

50
00:03:04,450 --> 00:03:05,870
thank you, Uncles and Aunties,

51
00:03:05,870 --> 00:03:07,750
for worrying about my mom's remarriage.

52
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:08,630
But now, we

53
00:03:08,630 --> 00:03:10,190
have settled in Shengcheng.

54
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:11,630
So we won't trouble you anymore.

55
00:03:11,630 --> 00:03:12,280
It's the New Year.

56
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:13,630
Everyone, please go back.

57
00:03:13,630 --> 00:03:14,550
Happy New Year.

58
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,190
Go prepare your New Year's goods.

59
00:03:16,190 --> 00:03:16,630
Yes, yes.

60
00:03:16,630 --> 00:03:17,490
Happy New Year.

61
00:03:18,079 --> 00:03:18,480
Hurry.

62
00:03:19,190 --> 00:03:20,150
Go back quickly.

63
00:03:21,030 --> 00:03:21,960
Come on, come on.

64
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:23,870
Xiaolan.

65
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:25,120
Let me tell you,

66
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,960
you should hurry up

67
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,120
with the recruitment.

68
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:30,240
Go back to Shengcheng
right after the New Year.

69
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:30,710
You see,

70
00:03:31,079 --> 00:03:33,120
you and your mother are living so well.

71
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:34,800
Those people are jealous.

72
00:03:35,079 --> 00:03:36,720
They won't give up easily.

73
00:03:36,910 --> 00:03:37,590
I'm back.

74
00:03:38,190 --> 00:03:39,920
Someone came to propose again?

75
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:42,930
Xiaolan,

76
00:03:43,310 --> 00:03:44,430
which family is it? Tell me.

77
00:03:44,430 --> 00:03:45,750
I'll go have a chat with them.

78
00:03:45,750 --> 00:03:46,750
Forget it, Uncle.

79
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:48,120
We don't come back often.

80
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:49,750
There's no need to argue with them.

81
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:50,840
We really should

82
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:52,180
get the recruiting done first.

83
00:03:52,180 --> 00:03:53,750
When we bring benefits to the village,

84
00:03:53,750 --> 00:03:55,030
people will naturally speak up for us.

85
00:03:55,030 --> 00:03:55,590
Exactly.

86
00:03:55,750 --> 00:03:57,030
Once our family makes money

87
00:03:57,030 --> 00:03:57,800
and thinks of everyone,

88
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:59,240
helping them live a better life,

89
00:03:59,240 --> 00:03:59,800
they'll naturally stand

90
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:00,840
on our side.

91
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:02,410
True.

92
00:04:02,890 --> 00:04:03,240
Let's go.

93
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:04,590
Let's go talk to the Chief.

94
00:04:04,590 --> 00:04:05,430
Unload the stuff then.

95
00:04:05,430 --> 00:04:06,090
Okay, okay.

96
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:09,030
Look.

97
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:10,840
Guangdong sausage.

98
00:04:11,470 --> 00:04:12,000
Nice.

99
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:13,820
Yong.

100
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,600
Thinking of the villagers

101
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:16,589
shows your kindness.

102
00:04:16,589 --> 00:04:17,360
Don't worry.

103
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:21,160
[Qijing Village Villagers Committee]

104
00:04:17,870 --> 00:04:18,920
As for the recruitment,

105
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:20,560
I'll definitely handle it for you.

106
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:21,120
Great.

107
00:04:21,510 --> 00:04:21,920
Later,

108
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:22,830
have them come to my house tomorrow

109
00:04:22,830 --> 00:04:23,390
for a meal.

110
00:04:23,390 --> 00:04:24,870
We'll discuss it properly.

111
00:04:24,870 --> 00:04:25,270
Sure.

112
00:04:25,730 --> 00:04:27,160
Once the people are picked,

113
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:27,800
I'll have them

114
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:28,830
come to your house.

115
00:04:28,830 --> 00:04:29,160
Good.

116
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:30,830
Xiaolan.

117
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:31,970
Don't worry.

118
00:04:32,190 --> 00:04:33,190
I told them all

119
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:34,340
not to meddle in

120
00:04:34,390 --> 00:04:35,590
your mom's business.

121
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:36,560
You two just

122
00:04:36,870 --> 00:04:38,360
have a peaceful New Year.

123
00:04:38,630 --> 00:04:39,630
Thank you, Chief.

124
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:40,950
By the way, Yong.

125
00:04:41,430 --> 00:04:42,800
Isn't Tao's cousin

126
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,260
coming back for the New Year?

127
00:04:44,260 --> 00:04:45,230
Tao's cousin?

128
00:04:46,270 --> 00:04:48,130
Since when does Tao have a cousin?

129
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:50,220
Zhou Cheng?

130
00:04:52,020 --> 00:04:52,750
Chief.

131
00:04:53,159 --> 00:04:54,600
Tao doesn't have a cousin.

132
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:56,400
That Zhou Cheng, actually he...

133
00:04:58,159 --> 00:04:59,510
I knew it long ago.

134
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:02,300
That kid seems nice.

135
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:04,220
He's a good match for Xiaolan.

136
00:05:05,220 --> 00:05:05,870
Xiaolan,

137
00:05:06,310 --> 00:05:07,190
next time he comes,

138
00:05:07,190 --> 00:05:08,070
introduce him

139
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:09,870
to the villagers properly.

140
00:05:11,270 --> 00:05:12,070
Sure.

141
00:05:12,310 --> 00:05:12,720
Okay.

142
00:05:13,190 --> 00:05:14,270
Come over in the next couple of days

143
00:05:14,270 --> 00:05:15,160
for a meal,

144
00:05:15,630 --> 00:05:16,680
so you can try

145
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:17,940
the Shengcheng cuisine.

146
00:05:17,940 --> 00:05:18,740
That's great.

147
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:20,680
I'll try the Shengcheng cuisine.

148
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:21,210
Alright.

149
00:05:21,270 --> 00:05:22,090
-Bye.
-Okay.

150
00:05:22,190 --> 00:05:22,520
Okay.

151
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:22,890
Okay.

152
00:05:22,950 --> 00:05:23,720
Take care.

153
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:25,830
Granny Yu.

154
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:26,970
You're back.

155
00:05:28,310 --> 00:05:29,070
When you weren't here,

156
00:05:29,070 --> 00:05:30,720
Zhou Cheng called to say

157
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:33,920
he's coming for a New Year visit
on the second day.

158
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:34,480
Really?

159
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:35,880
What else did he say?

160
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,950
To an old woman like me,

161
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:40,370
what is there to say?

162
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:42,830
If there's something
you want to hear from him,

163
00:05:42,830 --> 00:05:44,360
just call him back.

164
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:56,409
Is the phone burning your hand?

165
00:06:01,890 --> 00:06:02,970
Okay, let's go.

166
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:05,480
Be careful. Slow down. Slow down.

167
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:06,800
Watch out for your feet.

168
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:07,850
Careful. Careful.

169
00:06:07,850 --> 00:06:08,680
Careful. Good.

170
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:09,480
Yong!

171
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,260
Wait a moment. Come on.

172
00:06:12,730 --> 00:06:13,160
-Come on!
-Come on!

173
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:14,950
-Give us a hand, everyone!
-Give us a hand!

174
00:06:14,950 --> 00:06:15,800
-Come on, come on.
-Come on, come on.

175
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:16,510
Okay, okay.

176
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:17,680
Yong.

177
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:19,270
Uncle Da said
if we went to the city with you,

178
00:06:19,270 --> 00:06:20,280
we could make money,

179
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:21,200
so we came.

180
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:23,360
You can definitely make money,

181
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:25,390
but it will be hard work.

182
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:27,350
Can you handle the hardship?

183
00:06:27,390 --> 00:06:28,050
-Yes.
-Yes.

184
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,810
-We can.
-We surely can.

185
00:06:30,330 --> 00:06:31,790
Then move the chairs over.

186
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:32,560
Sit down, and we'll talk!

187
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:33,480
-Come on, come on!
-Come on, come on!

188
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:34,950
The legs of lamb are here.

189
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:36,950
Look at these great legs of lamb.

190
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:37,950
Look.

191
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:38,800
Really good.

192
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:41,070
Granny Yu,
how should we cook these legs of lamb?

193
00:06:41,070 --> 00:06:42,040
Braise one,

194
00:06:42,270 --> 00:06:43,870
and make soup with the other.

195
00:06:44,310 --> 00:06:45,370
You're a good cook.

196
00:06:45,510 --> 00:06:46,440
You make the soup.

197
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:48,159
Didn't we say we'd braise them yesterday?

198
00:06:48,159 --> 00:06:49,480
Why are we making soup today?

199
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:51,600
If Granny Yu says we should make soup,
we'll do it.

200
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:52,360
But I won't put

201
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:53,360
potatoes in.

202
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:55,560
Eating potatoes raises blood sugar.

203
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:57,090
You should be more careful.

204
00:06:58,030 --> 00:06:59,750
She nags more than a doctor.

205
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:00,840
Granny Yu.

206
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,560
Today, you are

207
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:04,000
acting a bit differently than usual.

208
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,060
It's a bit strange.

209
00:07:06,190 --> 00:07:06,920
Really?

210
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:09,660
Yong.

211
00:07:10,190 --> 00:07:12,190
I found these people strictly following

212
00:07:12,190 --> 00:07:13,320
your requirements.

213
00:07:14,270 --> 00:07:15,530
We all know each other.

214
00:07:15,640 --> 00:07:17,100
Happy New Year, everyone.

215
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:20,410
Have a taste.

216
00:07:20,410 --> 00:07:21,470
Let's eat and talk.

217
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,210
Listen to me.

218
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,390
These past few years,

219
00:07:24,390 --> 00:07:25,630
I've been in Shengcheng,

220
00:07:25,630 --> 00:07:27,360
renovating houses for people.

221
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:29,510
Business is getting better and better.

222
00:07:29,510 --> 00:07:31,160
Now I'm short of hands.

223
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:33,270
I need people I know well

224
00:07:33,270 --> 00:07:34,270
who can do the job.

225
00:07:34,890 --> 00:07:35,530
Naturally,

226
00:07:35,530 --> 00:07:37,120
I prefer folks from our village,

227
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:37,520
right?

228
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:39,830
-Right, right.
-Right, right.

229
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:40,800
Let me tell you.

230
00:07:40,830 --> 00:07:42,240
Even if you have bricklaying skills,

231
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:44,370
you have to start from scratch with me.

232
00:07:45,070 --> 00:07:46,670
When you first start with me,

233
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:48,770
I can pay you 10 yuan a day.

234
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:49,480
Ten yuan.

235
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:51,520
When you become a junior worker,

236
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:52,750
it's 13 a day.

237
00:07:53,810 --> 00:07:54,920
-Thirteen yuan!
-Thirteen!

238
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:56,480
When you become a senior worker,

239
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:59,070
I'll pay you 18 yuan a day!

240
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:01,950
I want to be a senior worker!

241
00:08:01,950 --> 00:08:03,120
I want to be a senior worker too!

242
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:05,160
Although we've never been to Shengcheng,

243
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:07,040
we've all done unskilled labor in Shangdu.

244
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:08,380
The wage Yong offers

245
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:09,270
is really fair,

246
00:08:09,270 --> 00:08:09,680
right?

247
00:08:09,700 --> 00:08:10,900
-Totally!
-Totally!

248
00:08:11,270 --> 00:08:11,870
Last year,

249
00:08:11,870 --> 00:08:12,920
I worked in the county town

250
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:14,320
and only made 8 yuan a day.

251
00:08:15,510 --> 00:08:17,120
Everyone understands the money situation,

252
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:17,520
right?

253
00:08:18,070 --> 00:08:19,720
Let me tell you something else.

254
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:20,750
The train tickets

255
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:21,570
are on me!

256
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:26,630
Everyone has

257
00:08:26,630 --> 00:08:27,480
ID cards now, right?

258
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,190
You all got them, right?

259
00:08:28,190 --> 00:08:29,630
-We got them.
-We got them.

260
00:08:29,630 --> 00:08:30,830
So for the tickets,

261
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:32,510
we don't need letters of introduction
anymore.

262
00:08:32,510 --> 00:08:33,770
It's more convenient.

263
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:35,080
That is so convenient.

264
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:35,880
That's great.

265
00:08:36,630 --> 00:08:37,159
Fengmei.

266
00:08:37,490 --> 00:08:38,549
What are you cooking?

267
00:08:38,549 --> 00:08:39,610
It smells so great!

268
00:08:40,130 --> 00:08:41,330
You'll find out soon.

269
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:43,250
I promise you'll eat and drink your fill.

270
00:08:43,250 --> 00:08:44,840
-Great!
-Great!

271
00:08:44,870 --> 00:08:46,200
Today, right here,

272
00:08:46,630 --> 00:08:48,030
enjoy the food and drink.

273
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:48,840
Then,

274
00:08:49,030 --> 00:08:50,030
go home and explain everything

275
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:51,550
clearly to your wives and children.

276
00:08:51,550 --> 00:08:52,670
Then we'll head out!

277
00:08:52,670 --> 00:08:54,320
-Okay!
-Okay!

278
00:08:54,390 --> 00:08:56,530
-Thanks, Yong!
-Thanks, Yong!

279
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:01,440
Is the meat ready?

280
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:02,550
It smells so good.

281
00:09:02,550 --> 00:09:03,350
Wait a moment.

282
00:09:03,670 --> 00:09:05,130
Let the sauce reduce a bit.

283
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:06,670
The food is almost ready, right?

284
00:09:06,670 --> 00:09:07,600
I think it's time

285
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,320
to start the feast.

286
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:09,240
It's time to eat.

287
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:10,240
What's the rush?

288
00:09:11,030 --> 00:09:13,430
Wait for your uncle
to settle the business.

289
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,240
Otherwise, in a bit,

290
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,410
they'll be drunk,

291
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:17,240
leaving the business unsettled

292
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:18,790
and bickering over nothing.

293
00:09:18,790 --> 00:09:19,390
True.

294
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:20,270
These men

295
00:09:20,270 --> 00:09:21,960
drink endlessly during the New Year.

296
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:22,670
Exactly.

297
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,440
Granny Yu,

298
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:28,840
why does it look like

299
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:30,440
